Collection.Name: Vitamin D, 25-Hydroxy
Collection.ClinicalDescription:
Vitamin D deficiency has been defined by the Institute of
Medicine and an Endocrine Society practice guideline as a
level of serum 25-OH vitamin D less than 20 ng/mL (1,2).
The Endocrine Society went on to further define vitamin D
insufficiency as a level between 21 and 29 ng/mL (2).
1. IOM (Institute of Medicine). 2010. Dietary reference
   intakes for calcium and D. Washington DC: The
   National Academies Press.
2. Holick MF, Binkley NC, Bischoff-Ferrari HA, et al.
   Evaluation, treatment, and prevention of vitamin D
   deficiency: an Endocrine Society clinical practice
   guideline. JCEM. 2011 Jul; 96(7):1911-30.

Collection.ClinicalDescription:
PATIENT HISTORY:
Family history of breast cancer in paternal aunt at age 48.

Baseline mammogram.

Mammo Screening Bilateral Digital: December 17, 2015 - Accession 
#: NBB15003032609
Bilateral CC and MLO view(s) were taken.
Technologist: Terri Smith, RT(M)
No prior studies available for comparison.

The breast tissue is comprised of scattered fibroglandular 
densities.  (25-50% glandular tissue.)  MAMMOGRAM FINDINGS: There
is no evidence of dominant mass, skin thickening, nipple 
retraction, architectural distortion or suspicious clustered 
microcalcifications. [ ]
IMPRESSION:See Assessment.

ASSESSMENT: Category 1: Negative.

This report was analyzed using CAD (computer aided 
detection).
RECOMMENDATION:
 Routine screening mammogram of both breasts in 1 year.
Interpreted by: Gretchen Smith     12/18/2015 4:16 PM

Signed by: Gretchen Smith     12/18/2015 4:17 PM
